While South Africans are still trying to come to terms with what stage 6 of load-shedding even means, Duduzane Zuma says the country should have listened to his father, Jacob Zuma. Duduzane claims that if the country had listened to his father, former president Jacob Zuma, the country's lights would still be on. Taking to Twitter, Duduzane said if at the time that his dad was president Eskom had been privatised, the mess that the country finds itself in could have been avoided.  He said the next step is privatisation, per his father advice. "The next step is privatisation. My father warned you about this president," he wrote. The next step is privatisation. My father warned you about this president. 